  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he said to me that a few research analysts we have, which we borrowed from the-- from the American Embassy in Paris, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] just are bringing me mainly things about the atrocities that are happen-- that Rosenberg was connected with, that the Nazis did.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'd like to get something on aggressive war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And can you find something on aggressive war in these documents?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I went out and got myself a drink and came back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that evening, the first day I was in Paris with-- with OSS, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I went up and I looked at these documents and I said, this is overwhelming.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I saw one document, which was a narrow one, about half the size of the others, and it said on the outside, [GERMAN], A-P-A Norway, Foreign Political Office, Norway.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Rosenberg, who had been the party foreign relations man-- not the state, that was von Ribbentrop and others-- would, being the party man who had liaison with pro-Nazis and-- and semi-fascists and fascists in other countries, he had this notebook on his dealings with Norway.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I pulled it down and opened it up to just before the invasion of Norway in April or May 1940.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And just before that invasion, Quisling, who was the-- who was the traitor of Norway, came down with a guy by the name of Hagelin and visited Rosenberg and was introduced to Hitler and so on.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they'd made some notions that eventually the Germans would occupy Norway.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, the Germans did shortly thereafter, and Quisling was made the approved Norwegian to run Norway under the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
